  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05/D3 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package carries adversarial weakener W-AR-05 (comparator absence/mismatch) instantiated as defeater D3 (undercutting via inference method mismatch): the primary validation result omits its comparedAgainst link entirely, while a secondary result references a comparator dataset collected under ventricular-assist device (VAD) operating pressures rather than CPB-range pressures, creating a plausibly deniable condition mismatch that undermines the relative-hemolysis-index acceptance criterion.",
